WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.300 --> 00:00:05.220
I'm going to call the workshop to order, and I

2
00:00:05.240 --> 00:00:08.780
will say, as this is a public proceeding,

3
00:00:09.240 --> 00:00:12.760
unless the Board of Education specifically votes to go into

4
00:00:12.800 --> 00:00:16.660
executive session, the... I have to take my glasses

5
00:00:16.720 --> 00:00:20.480
off so I can see this close. The public has the right to hear everything that is

6
00:00:20.520 --> 00:00:24.140
being said and to look at any exhibits that are being offered.

7
00:00:24.240 --> 00:00:28.040
Please notify us by raising your hand if you're unable to see or hear,

8
00:00:28.840 --> 00:00:32.000
or if you need an interpreter, as these

9
00:00:32.680 --> 00:00:35.540
people just announced, you can just come down.

10
00:00:35.920 --> 00:00:39.660
Somebody can come and sit with you and interpret as

11
00:00:39.700 --> 00:00:43.650
we're going along. So please, if you need interpretation,

12
00:00:44.460 --> 00:00:47.900
please come down and just speak with one of these

13
00:00:47.940 --> 00:00:49.140
people.

14
00:00:53.640 --> 00:00:56.840
So I'm going to ask the superintendent to

15
00:00:57.480 --> 00:00:59.100
call the roll.

16
00:01:05.261 --> 00:01:05.940
DeAngelis.

17
00:01:06.560 --> 00:01:06.880
Here.

18
00:01:07.320 --> 00:01:07.839
Dowling.

19
00:01:11.700 --> 00:01:12.220
Left.

20
00:01:13.540 --> 00:01:14.340
Feller.

21
00:01:14.380 --> 00:01:14.560
Here.

22
00:01:15.320 --> 00:01:15.780
Holman.

23
00:01:16.200 --> 00:01:16.340
Here.

24
00:01:16.760 --> 00:01:17.380
Richardson.

25
00:01:17.940 --> 00:01:18.100
Here.

26
00:01:18.540 --> 00:01:18.920
Rish.

27
00:01:19.160 --> 00:01:19.360
Here.

28
00:01:19.820 --> 00:01:20.260
Smith.

29
00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:20.680
Here.

30
00:01:23.920 --> 00:01:24.360
Thank you.

31
00:01:26.250 --> 00:01:26.540
Done.

32
00:01:28.720 --> 00:01:32.280
Thank you, everyone. First, I want to say that I made the

33
00:01:32.340 --> 00:01:36.300
change from this meeting from the Red Bank Community Center back

34
00:01:36.340 --> 00:01:39.080
to the lecture hall for two primary reasons.

35
00:01:39.660 --> 00:01:43.430
First, Red Bank had limited seating, and as you could see, that wouldn't

36
00:01:43.460 --> 00:01:47.360
work. The second was the audiovisual limitations.

37
00:01:47.480 --> 00:01:51.010
We could not guarantee that a video would be without glitches,

38
00:01:51.120 --> 00:01:54.320
so it made sense to move it back here.

39
00:01:54.360 --> 00:01:57.940
Given that, we did offer transportation from home,

40
00:01:58.460 --> 00:02:02.330
childcare availability in the library, and translation services,

41
00:02:02.760 --> 00:02:06.660
an effort to make this as accessible as possible, and I hope that creates

42
00:02:06.720 --> 00:02:08.420
a better situation for folks.

43
00:02:10.081 --> 00:02:13.940
I also wanted to say that I hear that there's a lot of

44
00:02:13.960 --> 00:02:17.740
emotion around these issues, and I'm hopeful that we can

45
00:02:17.820 --> 00:02:21.600
just be kind and show grace, myself included.

46
00:02:21.680 --> 00:02:25.660
Ultimately, the board needs to make a decision, and we're on a timeline,

47
00:02:26.460 --> 00:02:30.040
so while it may feel fast, it's a timeline we must follow, and

48
00:02:30.380 --> 00:02:32.620
Superintendent Entwistle will say more about this.

49
00:02:33.860 --> 00:02:37.740
I have received some emails that have taken me to task on a number of

50
00:02:37.800 --> 00:02:41.480
issues, so let me say that I do not intend

51
00:02:42.020 --> 00:02:45.820
to pit one school population against another, to give

52
00:02:45.880 --> 00:02:48.840
inaccurate information, or to create public shame.

53
00:02:50.080 --> 00:02:51.260
In my public comments,

54
00:02:52.080 --> 00:02:55.920
I did not call anyone a racist, although that has been said to me.

55
00:02:56.720 --> 00:03:00.360
I spoke of my own white privilege with no apology since I did

56
00:03:00.460 --> 00:03:01.440
nothing to earn it.

57
00:03:02.340 --> 00:03:05.940
I am surely not without faults, and I make mistakes every day.

58
00:03:06.960 --> 00:03:10.310
I went to dinner with friends on Friday night, and when I arrived, a friend asked,

59
00:03:10.380 --> 00:03:12.480
"How are you doing?" And I burst into tears.

60
00:03:13.240 --> 00:03:16.960
So I hadn't realized how much I was holding inside, but it all

61
00:03:17.060 --> 00:03:21.020
came spilling out. I'm a firm believer in Miguel Ruiz's "The

62
00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:21.920
Four Agreements,"

63
00:03:23.140 --> 00:03:25.500
and the third agreement is don't take things

64
00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:29.360
personally. But he is right when he says it's not easy.

65
00:03:30.360 --> 00:03:34.060
I have been tired, overwhelmed, and sleepless, and I know other board members

66
00:03:34.160 --> 00:03:34.860
feel the same.

67
00:03:35.800 --> 00:03:39.700
We may have different views, but everyone has an opinion, which does not

68
00:03:39.760 --> 00:03:43.560
mean we are biased. An opinion is a personal belief,

69
00:03:43.780 --> 00:03:47.740
perspective, or judgment, while a bias is a prejudice

70
00:03:47.780 --> 00:03:51.760
or unfair preference that slants information, often ignoring

71
00:03:51.769 --> 00:03:55.580
the evidence. I believe everyone up here is trying hard,

72
00:03:56.260 --> 00:03:59.960
doing the best that they can do, and we know you're doing the same.

73
00:04:01.340 --> 00:04:04.760
I thank folks who have appreciated the work this board

74
00:04:04.769 --> 00:04:08.660
does. That helps us move to the next email.

75
00:04:08.740 --> 00:04:12.680
Most of us have answered you, attending to school business barring other

76
00:04:12.720 --> 00:04:13.240
things.

77
00:04:14.100 --> 00:04:17.959
Many have visited schools, spoken to parents and teachers, and talked

78
00:04:18.019 --> 00:04:19.340
to other community members.

79
00:04:20.421 --> 00:04:23.880
Since I don't know many of you, and in turn, you don't know me, it might be helpful

80
00:04:23.940 --> 00:04:26.960
to hear some things. I grew up in Olney Beach.

81
00:04:27.420 --> 00:04:31.360
We were the only Italian family at the time, and my parents were first-generation

82
00:04:31.420 --> 00:04:34.560
immigrants, and English was not their first language.

83
00:04:35.720 --> 00:04:39.500
They moved from Scollay Square, now Government Center, in Boston,

84
00:04:39.960 --> 00:04:42.140
for the same reason many of you moved here,

85
00:04:42.950 --> 00:04:44.120
to give us a better life.

86
00:04:45.460 --> 00:04:49.340
I was the third of four children, and when I was about six, my dad ran for the

87
00:04:49.400 --> 00:04:53.300
school board against a 20-year incumbent, and we went

88
00:04:53.400 --> 00:04:56.800
door to door, each holding a sign. My sign said

89
00:04:56.880 --> 00:05:00.500
"my," because the signs read, "Vote for

90
00:05:01.120 --> 00:05:02.660
my dad."

91
00:05:03.820 --> 00:05:06.460
And he won the election and served for multiple terms.

92
00:05:07.020 --> 00:05:10.540
I was a difficult student, no surprise to anyone, questioning

93
00:05:10.600 --> 00:05:14.440
authority and often challenging my teachers and my dad, which

94
00:05:14.480 --> 00:05:15.240
was not easy.

95
00:05:16.620 --> 00:05:20.540
My parents were not college-educated but had wisdom that I only

96
00:05:20.600 --> 00:05:24.560
understood years later. I recently found a letter my dad wrote when

97
00:05:24.640 --> 00:05:28.240
I was in my first job in Jefferson as a speech-language

98
00:05:28.320 --> 00:05:32.280
pathologist, and it read, "Be sure you find out about the teachers union, and

99
00:05:32.320 --> 00:05:34.840
make sure you join." How did he know this?

100
00:05:35.600 --> 00:05:39.170
My mom and dad modeled political involvement and community engagement,

101
00:05:39.680 --> 00:05:43.660
and during my teaching years, I served on the MEA Board of

102
00:05:43.680 --> 00:05:47.660
Directors, I was chief negotiator, grievance chair, and finally, union

103
00:05:47.760 --> 00:05:49.300
president right here in South Portland.

104
00:05:50.480 --> 00:05:54.200
I served six years on the South Portland City Council, and I was

105
00:05:54.280 --> 00:05:58.080
mayor in 2012. But none of my community involvement is who I

106
00:05:58.220 --> 00:06:01.568
am. That's just what I do.Who I am is different.

107
00:06:02.228 --> 00:06:06.128
I love art, and my walls are covered art by friends, former

108
00:06:06.228 --> 00:06:10.178
students, and other artists. I was a drama queen in high school and college,

109
00:06:10.688 --> 00:06:14.608
and I ran an elementary drama program, and later the drama club at South Portland

110
00:06:14.628 --> 00:06:17.948
High School. I love to cook. I make a mean pizza.

111
00:06:19.188 --> 00:06:22.908
I love to laugh, and I gather with friends whenever I can.

112
00:06:22.968 --> 00:06:26.928
I was diagnosed with breast cancer in 1992, and my partner Joe

113
00:06:26.968 --> 00:06:30.568
took me to every chemo and radiation treatment, never leaving me

114
00:06:30.608 --> 00:06:30.968
alone.

115
00:06:32.788 --> 00:06:36.748
When he was diagnosed with mesothelioma in 2019, I did

116
00:06:36.788 --> 00:06:40.548
the same, only the outcome was different, and he died that

117
00:06:40.608 --> 00:06:44.398
year, my best friend, and every day something reminds me of

118
00:06:44.428 --> 00:06:46.678
him and reduces me to tears

119
00:06:47.528 --> 00:06:48.068
every day.

120
00:06:48.888 --> 00:06:52.448
He was a genius, an exquisite finish carpenter, an artist, and a

121
00:06:52.508 --> 00:06:55.428
musician, and I'm grateful for every moment we had.

122
00:06:56.828 --> 00:06:59.388
There is much more as there is about

123
00:07:00.688 --> 00:07:02.468
each one of us up here.

124
00:07:03.748 --> 00:07:07.708
I tell you this for no other reason other than to know something about

125
00:07:07.768 --> 00:07:09.588
me beyond this dais.

126
00:07:10.548 --> 00:07:14.488
Some emails said that I called some parents privileged, that I

127
00:07:14.528 --> 00:07:18.268
am not thinking of the entire community, that I was unkind to

128
00:07:18.328 --> 00:07:21.928
another board member, and please accept my apology,

129
00:07:22.188 --> 00:07:22.888
Member Holman.

130
00:07:24.028 --> 00:07:27.928
I am surely not perfect. I speak openly of my own privilege,

131
00:07:28.008 --> 00:07:31.488
which looms over me. I don't see myself as a white

132
00:07:31.548 --> 00:07:35.408
savior, but as someone with family and friends who have enriched

133
00:07:35.448 --> 00:07:39.408
my life immensely. I'm asking that we all try to be kind to

134
00:07:39.448 --> 00:07:43.308
each other, just kind. I do not think of myself as a

135
00:07:43.348 --> 00:07:45.968
good person, and certainly not better than others.

136
00:07:46.428 --> 00:07:48.508
Instead, I think of myself

137
00:07:49.908 --> 00:07:53.548
as someone who's trying every day to be a good person, just

138
00:07:53.588 --> 00:07:54.008
trying.

139
00:07:56.488 --> 00:07:58.848
I try only to acknowledge my white privilege,

140
00:07:59.728 --> 00:08:02.648
recognize it, and make different choices as a result.

141
00:08:03.368 --> 00:08:07.188
None of that makes me better. It took me a long time to even see it.

142
00:08:08.308 --> 00:08:12.088
I had a conversation recently with Member Davidson a couple of weeks

143
00:08:12.168 --> 00:08:14.988
ago, and I am in awe of his awareness.

144
00:08:15.188 --> 00:08:18.028
It far exceeds mine at twice his age.

145
00:08:18.808 --> 00:08:20.507
I learn from him, and I'm grateful.

146
00:08:21.688 --> 00:08:25.308
No one is doing this job because we want to hurt families or kids.

147
00:08:26.068 --> 00:08:29.688
Not everyone even takes the small $1,000 stipend.

148
00:08:30.428 --> 00:08:34.408
People do this job, run for public office, believing

149
00:08:34.448 --> 00:08:35.989
that they have something to offer,

150
00:08:37.108 --> 00:08:40.428
and wanting to make a difference and loving this community.

151
00:08:41.369 --> 00:08:45.138
Please keep that in mind as no one is intending to support anything

152
00:08:45.748 --> 00:08:48.898
but what that member believes is best for the community,

153
00:08:49.568 --> 00:08:51.448
even though you may see it differently.

154
00:08:52.348 --> 00:08:56.328
I have a saying that greets me every morning, "Make yourself useful doing

155
00:08:56.388 --> 00:09:00.128
something hard with good people." And please know that everyone up here,

156
00:09:00.648 --> 00:09:04.328
each of the nine of us, cares deeply and wants the very best,

157
00:09:04.768 --> 00:09:06.468
and I'm blessed to be with all of you.

158
00:09:07.088 --> 00:09:11.028
We can disagree, but underneath it all, we share a common goal,

159
00:09:11.628 --> 00:09:14.188
and let's see if we can work from there. Thank you.

160
00:09:17.088 --> 00:09:20.668
Can I address the board?

161
00:09:21.188 --> 00:09:24.488
Please. Superintendent Entwistle.

162
00:09:24.888 --> 00:09:28.068
This is an address to the board.

163
00:09:29.968 --> 00:09:33.788
You've seen the detailed overview of the superintendent's budget and will soon

164
00:09:33.848 --> 00:09:37.528
have an opportunity to dig into the deeper budget details.

165
00:09:38.068 --> 00:09:41.718
It is, in brief or in detailed format, an overall

166
00:09:41.828 --> 00:09:45.128
plan for spending, and it has, within certain

167
00:09:45.208 --> 00:09:49.008
parameters, flexibility should the board wish to make some adjustments

168
00:09:49.288 --> 00:09:50.028
down the road.

169
00:09:50.928 --> 00:09:54.748
Please be thinking about this as the board moves to approve the overall

170
00:09:54.808 --> 00:09:58.548
spending plan for the schools. The budget proposal

171
00:09:58.668 --> 00:10:01.848
is further a path back to building

172
00:10:01.948 --> 00:10:04.288
sustainability and financial health.

173
00:10:04.988 --> 00:10:08.748
It's a big step, and unfortunately, it does come

174
00:10:08.888 --> 00:10:12.488
at a cost to those impacted either by disruption

175
00:10:12.868 --> 00:10:13.988
or by job loss.

176
00:10:15.308 --> 00:10:18.668
And just one additional thought that I would like to share, if you will.

177
00:10:19.428 --> 00:10:21.827
Perhaps it will be a reminder to the board.

178
00:10:22.337 --> 00:10:26.298
It has to do with the rules around budget building and how those

179
00:10:26.348 --> 00:10:30.328
rules, no matter how helpful and needed, can sometimes

180
00:10:30.368 --> 00:10:34.208
create an awkwardness in the way information

181
00:10:34.348 --> 00:10:37.608
flows out. They have us foreshadowing plan

182
00:10:37.728 --> 00:10:41.708
changes prematurely and in public and cannot

183
00:10:41.748 --> 00:10:45.588
be moved on without further meetings and discussions at a

184
00:10:45.668 --> 00:10:48.848
later time, which do need to happen and will happen.

185
00:10:49.568 --> 00:10:53.348
In summary, I'm guessing that it will all not surprise you to

186
00:10:53.408 --> 00:10:57.048
hear as well that I do fully endorse this plan

187
00:10:57.428 --> 00:10:59.608
and encourage you to do the same. Thanks.

188
00:11:00.768 --> 00:11:03.928
Thank you, Superintendent Entwistle, and I'm going to

189
00:11:07.068 --> 00:11:09.028
go to Dr. Prince,

190
00:11:10.128 --> 00:11:12.028
or is Abigail going to start? Okay.

191
00:11:12.528 --> 00:11:15.328
Abigail Ketchem is our finance director. Thank you, Abigail.

192
00:11:24.708 --> 00:11:26.888
So I am Abigail Ketchem, finance director.

193
00:11:28.308 --> 00:11:32.248
If you could go back to that first slide, I just want to remind

194
00:11:32.288 --> 00:11:35.488
and point out that that budget detail, that is a link that's on our website.

195
00:11:35.568 --> 00:11:38.868
So you can click there from wherever you're at and look at the line item budget.

196
00:11:40.348 --> 00:11:40.988
Next slide.

197
00:11:43.248 --> 00:11:47.128
So tonight, we are going to present our FY27 current budget

198
00:11:47.188 --> 00:11:47.768
proposal.

199
00:11:48.628 --> 00:11:51.888
We're going to talk both about personnel reductions and non-personnel

200
00:11:52.128 --> 00:11:52.868
reductions.

201
00:11:53.788 --> 00:11:57.438
We are proposing to close one elementary school, and we will

202
00:11:57.468 --> 00:12:00.588
provide you with two different options for how that can look like,

203
00:12:01.368 --> 00:12:05.280
both by either reconfiguring or redistricting.And we're also

204
00:12:05.320 --> 00:12:08.960
going to take you through other reductions at the middle school,

205
00:12:09.240 --> 00:12:11.740
at the high school, and in our operations.

206
00:12:12.140 --> 00:12:15.020
Really, there are reductions everywhere throughout our budget.

207
00:12:16.060 --> 00:12:16.980
At the end of this,

208
00:12:19.020 --> 00:12:22.880
you all will have an opportunity to take some action if you choose to, if you feel

209
00:12:22.960 --> 00:12:26.620
you have enough information to do so, and that will be regarding a school

210
00:12:26.680 --> 00:12:30.600
closure, whether to reconfigure or redistrict along

211
00:12:30.640 --> 00:12:34.550
with the school closure, and you'll have a decision available to you

212
00:12:35.260 --> 00:12:37.780
for whether or not to accept this budget as a whole.

213
00:12:39.180 --> 00:12:40.240
Next slide.

214
00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:46.420
So we are in a

215
00:12:47.340 --> 00:12:50.240
incredibly painful situation,

216
00:12:51.960 --> 00:12:52.280
and

217
00:12:53.260 --> 00:12:56.820
it's worth noting that alongside all of this pain,

218
00:12:57.860 --> 00:12:59.980
we will still be a school district.

219
00:13:00.180 --> 00:13:04.020
We will still teach students, and our mission is the same,

220
00:13:04.680 --> 00:13:08.080
to teach our students. So we're not folding as a district.

221
00:13:08.340 --> 00:13:12.060
We will be smaller, but we will move forward.

222
00:13:13.780 --> 00:13:17.720
Our mission and our heart is for our students, and that's

223
00:13:17.760 --> 00:13:21.560
the same no matter what the reductions are.

224
00:13:23.420 --> 00:13:26.500
We are proposing losing 12% of our staff.

225
00:13:27.300 --> 00:13:31.000
We're closing an elementary school, and we cannot deny

226
00:13:31.740 --> 00:13:33.400
the pain that we're all in over this.

227
00:13:33.780 --> 00:13:37.760
This is the last thing me and any other of our leadership wants to

228
00:13:37.800 --> 00:13:41.540
be in. This is a very difficult time.

229
00:13:43.200 --> 00:13:46.460
Alongside that, a few things just to point out about our budget.

230
00:13:46.760 --> 00:13:50.640
I think the main thing is that we've taken a really close view,

231
00:13:50.680 --> 00:13:53.540
especially on the non-personnel side of the budget.

232
00:13:53.760 --> 00:13:55.740
The personnel side is fairly straightforward.

233
00:13:55.800 --> 00:13:58.260
Everybody moves on to their next step, their next

234
00:13:59.480 --> 00:14:03.240
increase. But on the non-personnel side, we've really focused on being

235
00:14:03.280 --> 00:14:04.000
realistic.

236
00:14:04.840 --> 00:14:08.740
We do have some under-budgeting in our current year, which has had an effect.

237
00:14:08.800 --> 00:14:11.690
It's part of our spending freeze. It's part of our story.

238
00:14:11.900 --> 00:14:15.500
And we've really focused on having as accurate and realistic

239
00:14:15.510 --> 00:14:18.860
projections and increases for things like electricity, for example.

240
00:14:20.440 --> 00:14:21.360
Next slide, please.

241
00:14:25.440 --> 00:14:28.340
So I've been here about almost nine months,

242
00:14:29.820 --> 00:14:30.980
and I hear a lot about

243
00:14:31.920 --> 00:14:33.120
what happened here,

244
00:14:34.220 --> 00:14:37.120
and I've gone through that same

245
00:14:40.120 --> 00:14:43.840
spiral with what happened here, and I don't know

246
00:14:43.860 --> 00:14:47.820
everything. But there are a few things that I think I do have

247
00:14:47.840 --> 00:14:48.620
a take on it,

248
00:14:49.500 --> 00:14:53.240
having looked in our books, having gone through fund balance year after year, and

