the child's community, part of their neighborhood, well, it seems that we're not

2796
02:46:38.478 --> 02:46:40.948
really considering ourselves one school system after all.

2797
02:46:41.898 --> 02:46:42.178
Thank you.

2798
02:46:43.178 --> 02:46:43.858
Thank you, Sam.

2799
02:46:45.658 --> 02:46:46.338
Yes, go ahead.

2800
02:46:50.718 --> 02:46:53.938
My name is Shay Cupid, and I'm the literacy specialist at Kayler School.

2801
02:46:54.838 --> 02:46:56.958
Surprised myself that I'm coming back up here.

2802
02:46:57.178 --> 02:47:00.198
My 10-year-old self wouldn't really believe that I'd be speaking to this large

2803
02:47:00.258 --> 02:47:03.138
group- ... and sharing my thoughts and my perspective,

2804
02:47:03.738 --> 02:47:07.438
especially when there may be contrast to others' experience

2805
02:47:07.498 --> 02:47:11.478
and opinions. But here I am because the moment we are in feels

2806
02:47:11.518 --> 02:47:13.148
pivotal, and the timing is urgent.

2807
02:47:13.838 --> 02:47:17.628
First, to the board, I hope you will continue to center your decisions on the

2808
02:47:17.678 --> 02:47:21.648
need to balance the budget while most importantly considering the structure that

2809
02:47:21.658 --> 02:47:25.447
would create the best possible learning conditions for all students moving forward.

2810
02:47:26.358 --> 02:47:30.248
To families and community members, I hope we can approach this moment with openness

2811
02:47:30.248 --> 02:47:34.098
and a willingness to work together, even when uncertainty feels high, which

2812
02:47:34.158 --> 02:47:37.978
in turn may bring up feelings of fear and unease, but also invites

2813
02:47:38.038 --> 02:47:41.398
us to listen more closely, ask questions, and support one another through the

2814
02:47:41.458 --> 02:47:42.018
process.

2815
02:47:43.318 --> 02:47:46.978
To my colleagues, I want to acknowledge the weight of what we've been carrying, not

2816
02:47:47.018 --> 02:47:50.538
just in recent weeks, but over a sustained period of change and loss.

2817
02:47:51.278 --> 02:47:55.178
We have all had to adapt, absorb new challenges, and keep showing up for students

2818
02:47:55.198 --> 02:47:57.598
and families through ongoing uncertainty.

2819
02:47:57.638 --> 02:47:59.978
It is heavy, overwhelming, and exhausting.

2820
02:48:01.798 --> 02:48:05.287
As a district, we have experienced significant losses for quite some time, and this

2821
02:48:05.318 --> 02:48:07.778
month in particular has been especially hard.

2822
02:48:07.818 --> 02:48:11.478
Like many of our schools, Kayler experienced immense loss this past week.

2823
02:48:12.118 --> 02:48:15.298
In many ways, it feels like as a district, we have reached what could be described

2824
02:48:15.338 --> 02:48:19.178
as rock bottom as we try to envision what comes next for our students,

2825
02:48:19.218 --> 02:48:21.338
our families, our staff, and our schools.

2826
02:48:22.258 --> 02:48:24.388
And yet, I say that not without hope.

2827
02:48:24.778 --> 02:48:28.358
I am an optimist at heart, and I have deep confidence in the dedicated

2828
02:48:28.398 --> 02:48:29.998
educators we have in South Portland.

2829
02:48:30.838 --> 02:48:34.578
If we are at rock bottom, then we also have an opportunity to begin rebuilding with

2830
02:48:34.618 --> 02:48:37.798
intention, with care, and with a shared commitment to moving forward.

2831
02:48:38.598 --> 02:48:41.988
I'm inviting us all to come to the process first with pause and reflection.

2832
02:48:42.618 --> 02:48:46.238
As we navigate what comes next, I am hopeful that as a community, we can consider

2833
02:48:46.278 --> 02:48:49.918
how we communicate, collaborate, question, and act from a shared belief

2834
02:48:50.458 --> 02:48:53.118
in growing a stronger community in partnership with one another.

2835
02:48:53.938 --> 02:48:56.958
One thing I've been reflecting on, especially as each week we have seen the

2836
02:48:56.978 --> 02:49:00.738
proposal of a different school closing, is that a school is not defined by its

2837
02:49:00.778 --> 02:49:04.438
building. It is defined by the people within it, the relationships, the

2838
02:49:04.478 --> 02:49:07.898
culture, and the shared work of educators, students, and families.

2839
02:49:07.938 --> 02:49:11.618
Those relationships are deeply meaningful and in many cases long-standing, and they

2840
02:49:11.658 --> 02:49:15.628
are worth honoring. However, that kind of environment is not tied

2841
02:49:15.658 --> 02:49:18.878
to a particular building. It can exist wherever we choose

2842
02:49:19.818 --> 02:49:23.668
to prioritize relationships, collaboration, and a shared commitment to students.

2843
02:49:23.668 --> 02:49:24.558
30 seconds remaining.

2844
02:49:24.638 --> 02:49:28.178
Collectively, we have the power to create that environment through any model when

2845
02:49:28.198 --> 02:49:31.038
we keep students and the community that supports them at the heart of our

2846
02:49:31.078 --> 02:49:31.698
decisions.

2847
02:49:34.018 --> 02:49:35.258
Melissa Scheltry, parent,

2848
02:49:36.498 --> 02:49:39.518
teacher, and taxpayer in South Portland, and I'm going to let you continue

2849
02:49:39.558 --> 02:49:40.118
listening to her.

2850
02:49:41.818 --> 02:49:44.918
I understand that the timeline for reconfiguration feels fast.

2851
02:49:45.118 --> 02:49:48.938
It's natural to question how we could be ready for students in four new

2852
02:49:49.038 --> 02:49:52.958
schools by the end of August. And in truth, I think the answer is

2853
02:49:53.018 --> 02:49:56.358
that ready is not a fixed endpoint we ever fully arrive at in

2854
02:49:56.418 --> 02:49:59.988
education. The work is ongoing. The to-do lists are never

2855
02:50:00.018 --> 02:50:02.518
complete. The learning never stops.

2856
02:50:02.538 --> 02:50:05.888
And still, we show up every day and do the work required to teach our

2857
02:50:05.918 --> 02:50:09.058
students. I have already shared my support for grade band

2858
02:50:09.078 --> 02:50:12.598
reconfiguration, and I won't use my time here to restate those points.

2859
02:50:13.078 --> 02:50:16.518
Instead, what I hope to emphasize is how we can move forward together from here.

2860
02:50:17.158 --> 02:50:20.488
As a profession, as a staff, and now as a community, we have experienced

2861
02:50:20.598 --> 02:50:23.598
division from many different directions in recent years and

2862
02:50:23.618 --> 02:50:27.598
months. My hope is that as we navigate this transition, we can shift our

2863
02:50:27.638 --> 02:50:31.498
focus toward asking questions such as, "What will create the best

2864
02:50:31.578 --> 02:50:35.278
possible learning conditions for students?" And, "How can we use a

2865
02:50:35.338 --> 02:50:38.958
solution-oriented approach to address the inherent constraints and valid

2866
02:50:39.038 --> 02:50:42.918
concerns families and staff will experience with a shift to our elementary school

2867
02:50:42.938 --> 02:50:46.518
structure?" And equally important, "How do we get to the best

2868
02:50:46.618 --> 02:50:49.458
possible outcome in the most challenging of circumstances

2869
02:50:49.518 --> 02:50:53.158
together?" There cannot be a single school of students, staff, and

2870
02:50:53.198 --> 02:50:56.608
families that faces the bulk of the change and challenges that will come from one

2871
02:50:56.718 --> 02:51:00.178
school closure. We are a community who has shown in the face of

2872
02:51:00.218 --> 02:51:03.848
adversity how we come together to do what is best for all members, and this should

2873
02:51:03.848 --> 02:51:07.768
not be any different.There are real challenges ahead

2874
02:51:07.808 --> 02:51:11.088
with the reconfiguration model, including the very real concerns about

2875
02:51:11.128 --> 02:51:15.108
transportation and the impact of moving away from K to four community structures

2876
02:51:15.148 --> 02:51:17.228
that many families and school communities value.

2877
02:51:17.928 --> 02:51:21.328
Rather than minimizing those concerns, I hope we can approach them collaboratively.

2878
02:51:21.808 --> 02:51:25.178
That means taking the time to ask thoughtful questions such as, how can the

2879
02:51:25.208 --> 02:51:29.168
district work with families, staff, and community members to develop solutions

2880
02:51:29.208 --> 02:51:32.028
that address these challenges in thoughtful and practical ways?

2881
02:51:32.788 --> 02:51:36.558
If we keep students at the center, and if we remain willing to listen, problem

2882
02:51:36.628 --> 02:51:40.468
solve, and build together, I believe we can move through this transition in a

2883
02:51:40.508 --> 02:51:44.378
way that not only meets logistical needs, but also strengthens our

2884
02:51:44.388 --> 02:51:47.908
sense of community and shared purpose of providing the best

2885
02:51:47.968 --> 02:51:50.858
educational opportunities for all the children in South Portland.

2886
02:51:51.668 --> 02:51:52.248
Thank you.

2887
02:51:52.348 --> 02:51:53.128
Thank you very much.

2888
02:51:55.168 --> 02:51:55.888
Next speaker.

2889
02:51:56.848 --> 02:51:57.208
Thank you.

2890
02:51:58.308 --> 02:52:02.128
Samantha Coatsir, South Portland taxpayer, educator, and parent.

2891
02:52:02.808 --> 02:52:06.168
Being a multidimensional stakeholder, I see all sides.

2892
02:52:06.518 --> 02:52:10.267
As a parent, I struggle to understand how we would manage multiple drop-off

2893
02:52:10.308 --> 02:52:13.707
locations if we have grade span schools.

2894
02:52:13.788 --> 02:52:17.708
As a taxpayer, we are stretched thin already, with childcare costs exceeding

2895
02:52:17.748 --> 02:52:21.648
our mortgage. As a human being, I do not want to perpetuate the

2896
02:52:21.668 --> 02:52:24.288
inequities that currently exist within our district.

2897
02:52:24.948 --> 02:52:27.208
And as a teacher, I can see the benefits of a

2898
02:52:27.248 --> 02:52:30.768
reconfiguration. I do not want to close a school.

2899
02:52:30.848 --> 02:52:34.648
No one does. But I don't want to be in the same position a

2900
02:52:34.708 --> 02:52:38.688
year, two years, or five years from now because we made the wrong decision in

2901
02:52:38.848 --> 02:52:39.728
2026.

2902
02:52:40.728 --> 02:52:44.558
Two things can be true at once. I strongly dislike the disruption this

2903
02:52:44.588 --> 02:52:48.348
will cause, and I can see the opportunity within a

2904
02:52:48.368 --> 02:52:52.248
pre-K through first grade and second through fourth grade reconfiguration.

2905
02:52:52.968 --> 02:52:56.948
If we must close a school for the '26 to '27 school year, which I

2906
02:52:57.048 --> 02:53:01.028
do believe is inevitable, I implore the board to support option A with

2907
02:53:01.048 --> 02:53:02.688
grade span reconfiguration.

2908
02:53:04.028 --> 02:53:08.008
Families want to feel heard. We want our concerns validated and addressed.

2909
02:53:08.608 --> 02:53:12.108
Including myself, my family is looking at three different elementary schools and a

2910
02:53:12.128 --> 02:53:14.688
daycare with the same arrival time.

2911
02:53:14.697 --> 02:53:17.668
This poses real logistical complications.

2912
02:53:17.708 --> 02:53:21.488
My husband will either need to sacrifice work time and ultimately income to

2913
02:53:21.498 --> 02:53:24.618
additional driving, and/or we will need to pay for some form of

2914
02:53:24.668 --> 02:53:28.448
childcare after finally exiting the financial grip of private pre-K.

2915
02:53:29.748 --> 02:53:33.588
Long bus rides before and after a full school day hardly feels like a great

2916
02:53:33.648 --> 02:53:37.558
solution. These concerns are real and should not

2917
02:53:37.588 --> 02:53:41.068
be dismissed. However, we also cannot remain

2918
02:53:41.128 --> 02:53:44.308
paralyzed by them. We need to be solution oriented.

2919
02:53:45.188 --> 02:53:48.808
Could transportation be designed with a priority to limit bus ride

2920
02:53:48.868 --> 02:53:51.988
times? Could school supported carpools be created?

2921
02:53:52.548 --> 02:53:55.868
Could a before care program for multi-children families be offered at the rec

2922
02:53:55.908 --> 02:53:59.818
center with busing from there? There are solutions, we just need to commit

2923
02:53:59.868 --> 02:54:00.588
to finding them.

2924
02:54:01.868 --> 02:54:05.828
Families value the continuity of a K to four model, the relationships, the

2925
02:54:05.888 --> 02:54:07.628
role models, the sense of community.

2926
02:54:08.288 --> 02:54:10.248
That feels like a loss with a reconfiguration.

2927
02:54:10.928 --> 02:54:14.488
But can we see beyond the problem? Could we create buddy school

2928
02:54:14.588 --> 02:54:18.518
systems, shared events, or reading buddy programs between the primary and

2929
02:54:18.588 --> 02:54:21.898
intermediate schools to build and maintain those connections?

2930
02:54:22.828 --> 02:54:25.108
Maybe these ideas are good, maybe they're not.

2931
02:54:25.128 --> 02:54:28.828
But the point is that families need to see empathy, proactivity, and a

2932
02:54:28.848 --> 02:54:30.028
willingness to problem solve.

2933
02:54:30.038 --> 02:54:30.797
Seconds remaining.

2934
02:54:31.288 --> 02:54:33.188
That is how you build trust during change.

2935
02:54:33.568 --> 02:54:37.388
If a plan to collect and address family concerns in a systematic way could be

2936
02:54:37.428 --> 02:54:41.288
created, we could move forward with a reconfiguration in a way that brings people

2937
02:54:41.348 --> 02:54:43.258
along rather than leaving them behind.

2938
02:54:44.088 --> 02:54:46.618
Initially, I leaned toward maintaining a K to four model.

2939
02:54:46.888 --> 02:54:49.308
But after listening and reflecting, I've changed my thinking.

2940
02:54:49.948 --> 02:54:53.808
If we simply close a school and redistribute students, those students are dropped

2941
02:54:53.868 --> 02:54:57.857
into existing social groups. For students who already struggle socially, that

2942
02:54:57.888 --> 02:54:58.738
becomes even harder.

2943
02:55:00.028 --> 02:55:00.868
That's three minutes.

2944
02:55:01.428 --> 02:55:01.768
Thank you.

2945
02:55:02.608 --> 02:55:06.228
Hi, I'm Mary Beth Fellers, a parent, resident, SOPO

2946
02:55:06.308 --> 02:55:06.668
teacher.

2947
02:55:06.948 --> 02:55:08.188
Just say you yield your time.

2948
02:55:08.488 --> 02:55:09.028
I yield my time.

2949
02:55:09.308 --> 02:55:09.788
Thank you.

2950
02:55:10.608 --> 02:55:11.608
A grade span model-

2951
02:55:11.668 --> 02:55:11.678
Thank you. No, thank you

2952
02:55:11.678 --> 02:55:15.548
... creates larger peer groups, increasing the likelihood that students can find

2953
02:55:15.568 --> 02:55:18.108
connection and belonging earlier. That matters.

2954
02:55:18.968 --> 02:55:22.508
This situation is not the fault of any one school community, so no

2955
02:55:22.668 --> 02:55:24.888
single community should bear the brunt of this burden.

2956
02:55:25.448 --> 02:55:29.058
This Hunger Game mentality is everyone sitting in their respective schools and

2957
02:55:29.128 --> 02:55:33.118
communities crossing their fingers, hoping and praying that anyone but them is

2958
02:55:33.148 --> 02:55:36.758
called as tribute, is an unhealthy and dangerous mindset for

2959
02:55:36.788 --> 02:55:40.408
families, educators, and students that are meant to function as one

2960
02:55:40.448 --> 02:55:40.918
community.

2961
02:55:41.888 --> 02:55:44.908
I know how it felt when I thought my school, Dyer, was closing.

2962
02:55:44.968 --> 02:55:48.618
I'd be lying if I didn't say I felt relief once it was off the chopping block,

2963
02:55:49.068 --> 02:55:51.768
but now I also deeply empathize with the Keeler community.

2964
02:55:52.688 --> 02:55:56.428
I beseech every South Portland community member to think of the students, families,

2965
02:55:56.488 --> 02:56:00.168
and teachers at each of the South Portland elementary schools with the

2966
02:56:00.208 --> 02:56:02.348
empathy that you would want if it was your school.

2967
02:56:03.368 --> 02:56:07.248
Widen your lens. With a closure being the only viable option to

2968
02:56:07.308 --> 02:56:11.188
address this budget crisis, you must consider reconfiguration so that

2969
02:56:11.248 --> 02:56:15.048
students and staff from one community are not thrust into other preexisting

2970
02:56:15.128 --> 02:56:18.828
communities, but rather, we could build new communities together in a meaningful

2971
02:56:18.888 --> 02:56:19.108
way.

2972
02:56:20.148 --> 02:56:22.368
I hear the argument that we don't have time to plan

2973
02:56:23.648 --> 02:56:26.508
and that we should close a school now and plan for next year.

2974
02:56:27.388 --> 02:56:31.228
That seems crazy to me. That approach will put us right back here

2975
02:56:31.238 --> 02:56:35.198
again with even more disruption. Teachers and families cannot

2976
02:56:35.228 --> 02:56:36.938
sustain this level of instability.

2977
02:56:37.378 --> 02:56:40.368
Teachers and students cannot be shuffled around two years in a row.

2978
02:56:41.068 --> 02:56:43.628
Closing a school without reconfiguration is a band-aid.

2979
02:56:43.888 --> 02:56:45.848
It addresses the symptom, not the problem.

2980
02:56:46.488 --> 02:56:50.348
Change next year would be hard and imperfect, but dragging it out would be

2981
02:56:50.368 --> 02:56:54.348
harder. Let's take advantage of the opportunity to do something good out of it

2982
02:56:54.688 --> 02:56:57.788
in one fell swoop, rip the Band-Aid, and let the healing begin.

2983
02:56:58.748 --> 02:57:01.748
A grade span model offers immense benefits for students.

2984
02:57:02.348 --> 02:57:06.158
It allows same grade teachers to collaborate daily, share expertise, and better

2985
02:57:06.228 --> 02:57:09.878
meet student needs. It allows for more flexible grouping and more effective

2986
02:57:10.008 --> 02:57:13.668
support for students who need it most, rather than attempting to solo the

2987
02:57:13.728 --> 02:57:17.608
Everest of differentiating and scaffolding instruction for a max capacity

2988
02:57:17.648 --> 02:57:21.544
classroom with high-end diverse needs.Right now, students in the

2989
02:57:21.604 --> 02:57:24.224
same district are not receiving equal opportunities.

2990
02:57:24.684 --> 02:57:27.254
That is an inequity-

2991
02:57:27.274 --> 02:57:27.284
30 seconds remaining

2992
02:57:27.303 --> 02:57:31.094
... we have the chance to address. The board's goal should be to choose an option

2993
02:57:31.124 --> 02:57:34.944
that addresses budget concerns, avoids overcrowding, and equalizes learning

2994
02:57:34.964 --> 02:57:38.684
conditions. I believe a grade span reconfiguration meets that

2995
02:57:38.704 --> 02:57:42.604
goal. Lastly, we must ensure that a strategic plan is put in place so

2996
02:57:42.624 --> 02:57:44.924
we do not find ourselves in this catastrophe again.

2997
02:57:45.624 --> 02:57:49.004
Change is hard, but if we approach it with empathy, thoughtful planning, and a

2998
02:57:49.044 --> 02:57:52.144
commitment to solutions, we can move forward together. Thank you.

2999
02:57:52.564 --> 02:57:52.964
Thank you.

3000
02:58:00.384 --> 02:58:02.244
Good evening. Can you hear me?

